.SH NAME
commitbrief-compress - Shrink COMMITBRIEF.md losslessly via the configured provider


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcommitbrief compress [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Compresses the repo's COMMITBRIEF.md by sending it to the configured
LLM provider with a compression-specific system prompt. Three levels
are available: light (~20-30% reduction, preserves examples),
balanced (~40-60%, default), aggressive (~60-80%, may merge similar
rules). The original is backed up under .commitbrief/backups/ with
an ISO timestamp before the file is replaced.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--dry-run\fP[=false]
	show the result summary; do not write or back up anything

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for compress

.PP
\fB--level\fP="balanced"
	compression level: light | balanced | aggressive

.PP
\fB--out\fP=""
	write result to this path instead of replacing COMMITBRIEF.md


